<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880308-0171 </DOCNO><HL> Merck Research Spending </HL><SO> </SO><CO> MRK </CO><IN> PHA </IN><DATELINE> RAHWAY, N.J.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Merck andamp; Co. said it plans to spend 15% more in 1988 on research and development than it did in 1987.    The drug maker expects the research and development budget to rise to $650 million in 1988 from $566 million.    In New York Stock Exchange composite trading yesterday, Merck's shares closed at $163.50, off 25 cents. </TEXT></DOC>